{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The final program parameters for bibliometric analysis were as follows: \"Time period = 2005-2024,\" \"Year Slice = 1,\" \"g-index = 25,\" and \"Top N% = 10.\"",
    "All the other parameters were selected to default.VOSviewer makes it possible to create bibliometric networks that illustrate interactions between various entities such as publications, keywords, institutions, or researchers.",
    "Furthermore, co-authorship analysis, bibliographic coupling, and co-citation generation are supported by VOSviewer.",
    "While CiteSpace offers unique statistical features, VOSviewer is a better tool for visualizing keyword co-occurrences.Thus, VOSviewer 1.6.19.0 (Leiden University, Holland) was employed to optimize the visualization of results [15,16].",
    "Bibliometric analysis was conducted based on the indications reported in the VOSviewer user manual [17]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
